{# templates/roadmaps/retirement/longevity-risk.html.twig #}
{% extends 'base-roadmaps.html.twig' %}

        {% block stylesheets %}
        {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_link_tags('retirement_css') }}
    {% endblock %}

    {% block javascripts %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('retirement_js') }}
    {% endblock %}

    {% block body %}
    <div class="container">
    <!-- article hero – retirement style -->
    <div class="article-hero animate" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e1a3a 0%, #2d2b55 100%);">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <div class="hero-icon" style="background-color: var(--retirement-color);">
                <i class="fas fa-hourglass-half"></i>
            </div>
            <h1>Longevity Risk <span>Planning for a 30‑Year Retirement</span></h1>
            <p class="hero-description">
                Thanks to medical advances, many of us will live longer than we expect. But a long life brings a financial challenge: making sure your savings last as long as you do. Discover how to plan for longevity risk.
            </p>
            <div class="phase-tag" style="background-color: rgba(108,92,231,0.2); color: #c3b9ff;">
                <i class="fas fa-layer-group"></i> Phase 2: Risk Management · 9 min read
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- introduction -->
    <section class="animate">
        <h2 class="section-title">🧓 What Is Longevity Risk?</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <strong>Longevity risk</strong> is the chance that you will outlive your retirement savings. With average life expectancies rising, a 65‑year‑old today can expect to live another 20 years – but half will live longer. Planning for a 30‑year retirement is becoming the new normal.
        </p>
    </section>

    <!-- key insights in rule‑grid style -->
    <div class="rule-grid animate">
        <div class="rule-item">
            <h4><i class="fas fa-chart-bar"></i> Life Expectancy Facts</h4>
            <p>A 65‑year‑old couple has a 50% chance that at least one will live to 90, and a 25% chance one will live to 95. Your plan should account for the possibility of a very long life.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-item">
            <h4><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Hedging Longevity</h4>
            <p>Strategies include delaying Social Security, annuities with lifetime income, maintaining some equities for growth, and being flexible with spending.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rule-item">
            <h4><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> The 30‑Year Horizon</h4>
            <p>If you retire at 65, planning for age 95 is prudent. That means your portfolio must sustain 30 years of withdrawals, possibly through market ups and downs.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- interactive tool: Longevity Planner -->
    <div class="card animate" style="margin: 40px 0;" id="longevity-tool">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Interactive: How Long Will You Live? What Will You Need?</h3>
        <p>Based on your age and gender, see estimated life expectancies and the nest egg required to fund a long retirement.</p>

        <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
            <div style="flex: 1 1 150px;">
                <label>Your current age</label>
                <input type="number" id="currentAgeLong" value="45" min="18" max="90" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 1 1 150px;">
                <label>Gender</label>
                <select id="gender" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                    <option value="male">Male</option>
                    <option value="female" selected>Female</option>
                </select>
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                <label>Desired annual spending ($)</label>
                <input type="number" id="annualSpendingLong" value="50000" step="1000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                <label>Expected annual return (%)</label>
                <input type="number" id="returnLong" value="5" step="0.1" min="0" max="10" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
            <button id="calculateLongevity" class="btn-outline">Calculate</button>
        </div>

        <div id="longevityResult" style="margin-top: 25px; padding: 20px; background: var(--light-color); border-radius: 12px;">
            <p>Fill in your details and click the button.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="pro-tip" style="margin-top: 15px; background-color: #e9e5ff; border-left-color: var(--retirement-color);">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> Life expectancy estimates are based on Social Security actuarial tables simplified. Your actual longevity depends on health, lifestyle, and family history. Always plan for a longer horizon than the average.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- quiz section -->
    <div class="quiz-container animate" data-page-id="{{ page.id | default(46) }}" style="background: #1e1a3a;">
        <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">📝 Test your knowledge: Longevity Risk</h3>

        <div class="quiz-question">1. What is longevity risk?</div>
        <div class="quiz-options" data-question="1">
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">The risk of dying too young</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">The risk of outliving your retirement savings</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">The risk that inflation will erode your savings</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">The risk of market downturns</div>
        </div>

        <div class="quiz-question">2. A 65‑year‑old couple has roughly what chance that at least one will live to 90?</div>
        <div class="quiz-options" data-question="2">
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">10%</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">50%</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">75%</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">90%</div>
        </div>

        <div class="quiz-question">3. Which of the following is NOT a good strategy to mitigate longevity risk?</div>
        <div class="quiz-options" data-question="3">
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Delaying Social Security benefits</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Purchasing a lifetime annuity</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Withdrawing aggressively in early retirement</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Maintaining some stocks for growth</div>
        </div>

        <div class="quiz-question">4. If you retire at 65, planning for a 30‑year retirement means you should plan to fund withdrawals until age:</div>
        <div class="quiz-options" data-question="4">
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">75</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">85</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">95</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">100</div>
        </div>

        <div class="quiz-question">5. Annuities can help with longevity risk because they:</div>
        <div class="quiz-options" data-question="5">
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Guarantee high returns</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Are free</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Provide guaranteed lifetime income</div>
            <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Are not subject to inflation</div>
        </div>

        <div class="quiz-actions">
            <button id="quiz-submit" class="btn" style="background-color: var(--retirement-color);">Get score & submit</button>
        </div>
        <div class="quiz-result"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- next steps in Phase 2 (Risk Management) -->
    <section style="margin: 60px 0;">
        <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: center;">📘 Continue Phase 2: Risk Management</h2>
        <div class="next-steps">
            <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'retirement', slug: 'inflation-silent-killer' }) }}" class="next-card">
                <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
                <h3>Inflation: Silent Killer</h3>
                <p>How inflation erodes your purchasing power.</p>
            </a>
            <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'retirement', slug: 'market-risk-sequence' }) }}" class="next-card">
                <i class="fas fa-wave-square"></i>
                <h3>Market Risk & Sequence</h3>
                <p>Why the order of returns matters near retirement.</p>
            </a>
            <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'retirement', slug: 'healthcare-ltc' }) }}" class="next-card">
                <i class="fas fa-notes-medical"></i>
                <h3>Healthcare & LTC</h3>
                <p>Medical costs can derail retirement. Be prepared.</p>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
